<L>__{interior o'rourke's night (later)}
<A>__{galvin and laura are in a booth. the remains of a dinner and drinks around them. they are both smoking cigarettes, intent on each other. both a little drunk.}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{the weak, the weak have got to have somebody to fight for them. isn't that the truth? you want another drink?}
<C>__{laura}
<D>__{i think i will.}
<A>__{galvin motions "another round" to the bartender.}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{jimmy!}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{that's why the court exists. the court doesn't exist to give them justice, eh? but to give them a chance at justice.}
<C>__{laura}
<D>__{and are they going to get it?}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{they might. yes. that's the pointerior.. is that they might... you see, the jury wants to believe. they're all cynics, sure, because they want to believe. i have to go in there tomorrow to find twelve people to hear this case. i'm going to see a hundred people and pick twelve. and every one of them it's written on their face, 'this is a sham. there is no justice...' but in their heart they're saying, 'maybe... maybe...'}
<C>__{laura}
<D>__{maybe what?}
<C>__{galvin}
<P>__{(beat)}
<D>__{maybe i can do something right.}
<C>__{laura}
<D>__{and is that what you're going to do?}
<P>__{(a beat)}
<D>__{is that what you're going to do...?}
<C>__{galvin}
<D>__{that's what i'm going to try to do.}
